article_title: OPEC Ministers Agree to Maintain Output Quota
article_text:
VIENNA—Delegates of the Organization of the Petroleum Exporting Countries agreed to roll over the group's production quota, maintaining the group's current official production output.

The decision comes despite concerns over adequate global supply. Libya has struggled to lift its output amid political turmoil in the country. Meanwhile, global growth—and by extension, oil demand—has been picking up.
